6. Test Scenarios
6.1 Functional Tests
[‚úì] Validate correct response for known valid ISBN-10


[‚úì] Validate correct response for invalid ISBN-10


[‚úì] Verify behavior with ISBN ending in X


[‚úì] Test with lowercase x if allowed


[‚úì] Validate handling of null, empty string, special characters


6.2 Protocol/Transport Tests
[‚úì] Send valid request over SOAP 1.1 and assert proper response


[‚úì] Send valid request over SOAP 1.2 and assert proper response


[‚úì] Send valid request using JSON format and verify behavior


6.3 Negative Tests
[‚úì] Malformed SOAP envelope


[‚úì] Missing sISBN element


[‚úì] Invalid Content-Type


[‚úì] Non-numeric or alphanumeric ISBNs


[‚úì] Long payloads (DoS-type check)


6.4 Response Validation
[‚úì] HTTP 200 status check


[‚úì] Content-Type matches the protocol


[‚úì] XML/JSON schema matches documented structure


[‚úì] Boolean response is correct (true/false)


6.5 Performance Tests (Optional)
[‚úì] 100 concurrent requests ‚Äî should not fail or delay


[‚úì] Average response time under 500ms



7. Test Approach
Phase
Tool
Description
Manual Testing
Postman, SOAP UI
Manual execution of all scenarios across protocols
Automation
Python + zeep / Java + TestNG
Automate basic validation using scripts
Load Testing
JMeter / Locust
Optional stress testing with varied payloads


8. Roles & Responsibilities
Role
Responsibility
QA Engineer
Design & execute test cases
Automation Engineer
Automate SOAP/JSON scenarios
Developer (Optional)
Fix backend issues based on test results


9. Entry and Exit Criteria
Entry Criteria:
API documentation is available


Endpoint is stable and responsive


Test environment is accessible


Exit Criteria:
All functional and negative test cases executed


All critical defects resolved


API response verified across all supported protocols



10. Risks & Mitigation
Risk
Mitigation
Service downtime
Check availability before execution
Invalid/missing documentation
Use actual responses to build test cases
Protocol mismatch
Test against all Content-Type variations


11. Sample SOAP Request (SOAP 1.1)
POST /services/isbnservice.wso HTTP/1.1
Host: webservices.daehosting.com
Content-Type: text/xml; charset=utf-8

<soap:Envelope xmlns:soap="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/">
  <soap:Body>
    <IsValidISBN10 xmlns="http://webservices.daehosting.com/ISBN">
      <sISBN>0306406152</sISBN>
    </IsValidISBN10>
  </soap:Body>
</soap:Envelope>


